            {
                "name": "Soulbound Homunculi",
                "type": "section",
                "sections": [],
                "text": "Most homunculi use a dose of their creator\u2019s blood as their spark of life, but it\u2019s possible to use a technique similar to that used in the crafting of a <a aonid=\"383\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">soulbound doll</a> to give a homunculus a personality and the semblance of life. These homunculi gain the soulbound trait, can speak, and do not have a special link to a creator, yet the process tends to warp the soul used so that, more often than not, what rises in the new homunculus body is a parody of its prior life. As such, soulbound homunculi are generally created by cruel spellcasters as a method of humiliating and tormenting vanquished enemies.",
